															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250809" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1465604975 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Jun 2016 00:29</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2522225">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Pershmerga</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Literally &quot;those who face death&quot;, which may be the best name for a milita currently in use anywhere today. These guys are absolutely terrible at guard duty, smoke like chimneys, and they all have like six cell phones for some inexplicable reason, otherwise way better in a fight then the Iraqi Army, IME.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Tawûsê Melek</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Interestingly enough, Yezidism is related to Gnosticism and Tawûsê Malek is essentially the head Archon whom God left to rule the universe in his name, equivalent to the Ophite Yaldaboath, who should be familiar to readers here, but rather than be a jerk about it Tawûsê Malek is trying to do the best job he can.</p>
<p>Also in my experience, because Yezidism is a mystery cult, and persecuted besides, educated Westerners are actually likely to know more about the theology of the faith than most Kurds, even many Yezidis, who haven't been inducted into the mysteries.</p>

